1 Auth ority for the purposes described in subsection B of this
2 section. Expenditures from said fund shall be made upon warrants
3 issued by the State Treasurer against claims filed as prescribed by
4 law with the Director of the Office of Management and Enterprise
5 Services for approval and payment.
6 B. There is hereby created at the Oklahoma Health Care
7 Authority the Intergenerational Education Program. The Program
8 shall be a competitive grant program with the purpose of
9 facilitating improvements in nursing facilitates, to expand the
10 number of intergenerational education programs in this state,
11 embodying collaboration between nursing facilities participating in
12 Oklahoma's Medicaid Program and public school districts in this
13 state. The Authority shall utilize funds available from the
14 Intergenerational Education Revolving Fund created in subsection A
15 of this section to implement the Program.
16 C. The Oklahoma Health Care Authority shall establish grant
17 eligibility criteria and an associated application process. Such
18 criteria shall establish minimum standards for facility eligibility
19 and award amounts.
20 D. Grant awards authorized under the provisions of this act may
21 be awarded in the form of rate adjustments to qualifying nursing
22 facilities participating in Oklahoma's Medicaid Program.
23 E. No amount of award shall be authorized under this act that
24 would exceed the cumulative total of funds directed for deposit to
